Management
Hubert C. Anderson
Cable Address
Manhoco - Manila
Manila, Philippines
March 5th
Dearest Debs;
Just a few lines to let you know that I had a fine trip down
this morning, met the Clipper which arrived
at two oclock and have
been with George Sellett ever
since. He saw the
girls twice in Hono-
lulu, once for tiffin and once at dinner.
Said they were both hav-
ing a grand time, that everyone was crazy abouy them and that they
were most enthusiastic about the trip from Manila. George said they
were scheduled to leave for the Island of Hawaii the day he was orig-
inally due to start out here and that when the plane was
delayed, he
called up the girls at the hotel and found that they had checked out,
so he assumes that they made the trip. George couldn't get over how
well the girls looked and said that he had never before realized just
how beautiful Frances was - he didn't mention Bo in that category but
said plenty about her personality. He saw Gene Sellers at Midway and
she told him that she was going back on the same ship with F and B.
that seemed to be some comfort to her - am not so sure that the girls
will find
it so convenient.
No letter from F or B here addressed to PAA. I am awfully
disappointed for I was looking forward to some direct news from them.
You will just have to keep whatever letters you receive until I re-
turn. You might forward letters to Manila, marked hold for H. M.B. so
i can read
get back.
Lots of love. Must chase out to
see Mrs. Bert Hall now.
Got vacin-
ated this AM by Doc Howard Smith.
Віх
